+# TypeScript Style Guide
+
+This document outlines coding conventions for the TensorFlow.js Models repository.
+
+## General Principles
+
+1. **Type Safety First**: Always prefer explicit types over `any`
+2. **Strict Equality**: Use `===` and `!==` instead of `==` and `!=`
+3. **Null Safety**: Use strict null checks, avoid `!= null` patterns
+4. **No Side Effects**: Avoid global state mutations
+5. **Code Reuse**: Use shared utilities instead of duplicating code
+
+## TypeScript Best Practices
+
+### Types and Interfaces
+
+```typescript
+// Good: Explicit types
+function processImage(input: HTMLImageElement): tf.Tensor3D {
+  return tf.browser.fromPixels(input);
+}
+
+// Bad: Using 'any'
+function processImage(input: any): any {
+  return tf.browser.fromPixels(input);
+}
+```
+
+### Null Checks
+
+```typescript
+// Good: Explicit null/undefined checks
+if (value !== null && value !== undefined) {
+  // Use value
+}
+
+// Bad: Loose equality
+if (value != null) {
+  // Use value
+}
+```
+
+### Object Property Checks
+
+```typescript
+// Good: Use 'in' operator
+if ('property' in object) {
+  // Use object.property
+}
+
+// Bad: hasOwnProperty
+if (object.hasOwnProperty('property')) {
+  // Use object.property
+}
+```
+
+### Type Guards
+
+```typescript
+// Good: Proper type guards
+function isTensor(input: unknown): input is tf.Tensor {
+  return input instanceof tf.Tensor;
+}
+
+// Use it
+if (isTensor(input)) {
+  // TypeScript knows input is tf.Tensor here
+}
+```
+
+## Code Organization
+
+### Import Order
+
+1. Node built-ins (e.g., `import * as fs from 'fs'`)
+2. External dependencies (e.g., `import * as tf from '@tensorflow/tfjs-core'`)
+3. Internal shared utilities (e.g., `import {scalePose} from '@tensorflow-models/shared'`)
+4. Local imports (e.g., `import {MyClass} from './my-class'`)
+
+### File Structure
+
+```typescript
+// 1. License header
+/**
+ * @license
+ * Copyright ...
+ */
+
+// 2. Imports
+import * as tf from '@tensorflow/tfjs-core';
+import {MyType} from './types';
+
+// 3. Constants
+const DEFAULT_VALUE = 10;
+
+// 4. Types/Interfaces
+export interface Config {
+  value: number;
+}
+
+// 5. Private functions
+function helperFunction() {
+  // ...
+}
+
+// 6. Exported functions/classes
+export class MyModel {
+  // ...
+}
+```
+
+## Documentation
+
+### JSDoc Comments
+
+```typescript
+/**
+ * Processes an image and returns predictions.
+ *
+ * @param input The input image to process
+ * @param config Optional configuration for processing
+ * @returns Array of predictions with scores
+ */
+export async function predict(
+    input: ImageInput,
+    config?: PredictConfig): Promise<Prediction[]> {
+  // Implementation
+}
+```
+
+### Inline Comments
+
+- Use comments to explain **why**, not **what**
+- Keep comments up-to-date with code changes
+- Avoid obvious comments
+
+```typescript
+// Good: Explains reasoning
+// Use synchronous NMS to maintain API compatibility
+const result = tf.image.nonMaxSuppression(boxes, scores, maxBoxes);
+
+// Bad: States the obvious
+// Call nonMaxSuppression function
+const result = tf.image.nonMaxSuppression(boxes, scores, maxBoxes);
+```
+
+## Error Handling
+
+### Validation
+
+```typescript
+// Good: Use shared validation utilities
+import {validateRange, validateNotNull} from '@tensorflow-models/shared';
+
+function setThreshold(value: number): void {
+  validateRange(value, 0, 1, 'threshold');
+  this.threshold = value;
+}
+
+// Good: Custom error messages
+if (predictions.length === 0) {
+  throw new Error('No predictions found. Ensure model is loaded.');
+}
+```
+
+### Try-Catch
+
+```typescript
+// Good: Specific error handling
+try {
+  const result = await model.predict(input);
+  return result;
+} catch (error) {
+  if (error instanceof InvalidInputError) {
+    console.error('Invalid input provided:', error.message);
+  }
+  throw error;
+}
+```
+
+## Performance
+
+### Tensor Memory Management
+
+```typescript
+// Good: Use tf.tidy for automatic cleanup
+const result = tf.tidy(() => {
+  const normalized = tf.div(input, 255);
+  return tf.square(normalized);
+});
+
+// Bad: Manual disposal (error-prone)
+const normalized = tf.div(input, 255);
+const result = tf.square(normalized);
+normalized.dispose();
+```
+
+### Avoid Unnecessary Operations
+
+```typescript
+// Good: Early return if no changes needed
+function scalePoses(poses: Pose[], scale: number): Pose[] {
+  if (scale === 1) return poses; // No scaling needed
+  return poses.map(p => scalePose(p, scale));
+}
+```
+
+## Testing
+
+### Test Structure
+
+```typescript
+describe('ModelName', () => {
+  let model: ModelClass;
+
+  beforeEach(() => {
+    model = new ModelClass();
+  });
+
+  afterEach(() => {
+    model.dispose();
+  });
+
+  it('should predict with valid input', async () => {
+    const input = createTestImage();
+    const result = await model.predict(input);
+    expect(result).toBeDefined();
+    expect(result.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);
+  });
+});
+```
+
+## Shared Utilities
+
+Use shared utilities to avoid code duplication:
+
+```typescript
+import {
+  scalePose,
+  getInputSize,
+  validateConfidenceThreshold
+} from '@tensorflow-models/shared';
+
+// Instead of reimplementing these functions
+```
+
+## Configuration
+
+### TypeScript Config
+
+- Use strict mode flags in `tsconfig.json`
+- Target ES2015 or later for better performance
+- Enable all strict null checks
+
+### Linting
+
+- Follow TSLint rules defined in `tslint.json`
+- Run linter before committing: `yarn lint`
+- Fix auto-fixable issues: `yarn lint --fix`
+
+## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
+
+### ❌ Global State Mutation
+
+```typescript
+// Bad: Mutating global objects
+const oldWarn = console.warn;
+console.warn = () => {};
+// ... do something
+console.warn = oldWarn;
+```
+
+### ❌ Using `any`
+
+```typescript
+// Bad: Loses type safety
+function process(input: any): any {
+  return input.value;
+}
+```
+
+### ❌ Suppressing TypeScript Errors
+
+```typescript
+// Bad: Hides real issues
+// @ts-ignore
+const result = dangerousOperation();
+```
+
+### ❌ Loose Equality
+
+```typescript
+// Bad: Type coercion
+if (value == null) { }
+
+// Good: Explicit
+if (value === null || value === undefined) { }
+```
+
+## Resources
+
+- [TypeScript Handbook](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/)
+- [TensorFlow.js API](https://js.tensorflow.org/api/latest/)
+- [Google TypeScript Style Guide](https://google.github.io/styleguide/tsguide.html)
