+# Shared Utilities
+
+This directory contains shared utility functions and helpers used across multiple TensorFlow.js model packages.
+
+## Modules
+
+### pose_utils.ts
+Common functions for pose manipulation including:
+- `scalePose()` - Scale a single pose by given factors
+- `scalePoses()` - Scale multiple poses
+- `flipPoseHorizontal()` - Flip a pose horizontally
+- `flipPosesHorizontal()` - Flip multiple poses horizontally
+
+### tensor_utils.ts
+Tensor operation utilities including:
+- `toTensorBuffers3D()` - Convert 3D tensors to buffers
+- `isTensor()` - Type guard for tensors
+- `getInputTensorDimensions()` - Get dimensions from various input types
+- `toInputTensor()` - Convert various inputs to 4D tensor
+
+### image_utils.ts
+Image manipulation utilities including:
+- `getInputSize()` - Get size from image-like elements
+- `resizeAndNormalize()` - Resize and normalize images
+- `padToTargetSize()` - Pad images to target dimensions
+
+### calculators/
+Advanced calculation utilities for pose and hand tracking.
+
+### filters/
+Smoothing and filtering utilities for temporal data.
+
+## Usage
+
+Import shared utilities in your model package:
+
+```typescript
+import { scalePose, flipPoseHorizontal } from '@tensorflow-models/shared';
+```
+
+## Benefits
+
+- **Code Reusability**: Avoid duplicating common logic across packages
+- **Consistency**: Ensure consistent behavior across all models
+- **Maintainability**: Single source of truth for common operations
+- **Type Safety**: Properly typed interfaces and functions
